Trip Snapshot

A relaxed, food-forward Christmas escape for you, your wife, and your newborn all within an easy walk of the best holiday spots in Center City.
Dates
Fri Dec 12 Sat Dec 13
Hotel
Canopy by Hilton, Center City
Drive Time
3 hours from Leesburg
Vibe
Christmas Market + Foodie

The plan is deliberately light: no rigid schedule, everything stroller-friendly, and all your wow moments markets, lights, food within about a 10minute walk of the hotel.

Friday Arrival & Christmas Village

Ease into the city, get settled with the baby, then walk straight into a European-style Christmas market as the lights come on.
10:00 AM
Depart Leesburg, VA
Aim for one relaxed stop for feeds/diapers; no rush, arrival between 1:001:30 PM is perfect.
1:30 PM
Check-In Canopy by Hilton
Valet the car so you dont have to think about parking. Head up to your King Studio Suite, unpack, and let everyone decompress.
2:004:00 PM
Room Reset & Nap Window
Feed the baby, dim the lights, and treat this as a soft landing buffer before heading back out.
4:00 PM
Walk to LOVE Park & City Hall
Stroller-friendly stroll straight into Christmas Village as the sky starts to dim and the lights pop.
5:006:30 PM
Christmas Village & Dinner
Graze on bratwurst, raclette, and sweets in the market or slip to a nearby spot in Midtown Village (Lolita, Double Knot, Vedge) for a seated early dinner.
Evening
Dilworth Park Lights & Back to the Canopy
Take the scenic route back via Dilworth Parks winter lights, then head up to the room for bedtime and a quiet night in.

Saturday Breakfast & Wanamaker Light Show

A slow morning built around great food and one last iconic Christmas moment before heading home.
8:30 AM
Breakfast Nearby
Walk to Reading Terminal Market for coffee, pastries, or a proper breakfast or try Middle Child for an excellent breakfast sandwich.
10:00 AM
Wanamaker Light Show
Step into Macys Grand Court for the classic multi-story light show and organ music. Indoors, warm, and stroller-friendly.
11:30 AM
Head Back to Leesburg
Check out, retrieve the car, and roll home with enough buffer before evening routines.

Where Youll Be

A quick visual tour of your tiny Christmas world everything within an easy loop around Center City.

Your core loop: Canopy hotel Reading Terminal for food LOVE Park & City Hall for Christmas Village Wanamaker light show inside Macys back to the hotel. No car needed once you arrive.

Food & Moments to Look Forward To

A few anchor experiences that will make the trip feel special while still being gentle with a newborn.
  • Sharing German-style street food and hot drinks together in the glow of Christmas Village lights.
  • Browsing stalls with the stroller while live music and city sounds blend into a soft background.
  • Letting yourselves be tourists for a day at Reading Terminal donuts, sandwiches, sweets, and people-watching.
  • Standing under the Wanamaker light show with your newborn, starting a little Christmas tradition as a family.
